						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into one of the temple kitchens on the hill.</p>						

						<p>Of these miscellaneous writings, some record the signatures of the Dutch officers who visited this place in the 17th and 18th centuries and some, in Tamil and Telugu, record the donations of South Indians.</p>						

